      "content": "i get that, but isn't there also a lot of data suggesting that stricter sentencing actually helps reduce crime rates by making people think twice? it feels like the \"root causes\" argument is sometimes used to justify not doing anything about immediate public safety issues. what's the actual consensus on whether deterrence works?",
